Third-party components bundled or linked at distribution time
================================================================

----------------------------------------------------------------
libcoraza
----------------------------------------------------------------
The pycoraza wheel links against (and `auditwheel repair` bundles into
`pycoraza.libs/`) `libcoraza.so`, the C shared library produced by the
Coraza project at https://github.com/corazawaf/libcoraza.

Copyright OWASP Coraza authors and contributors.
Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0.
See THIRD_PARTY_LICENSES/libcoraza-LICENSE.

----------------------------------------------------------------
Coraza
----------------------------------------------------------------
libcoraza embeds the Coraza WAF engine, the Go module developed at
https://github.com/corazawaf/coraza.

Copyright OWASP Coraza authors and contributors.
Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0.
See THIRD_PARTY_LICENSES/coraza-LICENSE.

----------------------------------------------------------------
OWASP CRS (Core Rule Set)
----------------------------------------------------------------
pycoraza ships a copy of the OWASP CRS rule files under
`pycoraza/coreruleset/rules/`. CRS is developed at
https://github.com/coreruleset/coreruleset.

Copyright OWASP CRS Project and contributors.
Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0.
See THIRD_PARTY_LICENSES/coreruleset-LICENSE.

================================================================
Notes
================================================================

- The pinned upstream tags for libcoraza, the embedded Coraza module,
  and the CRS rule set are recorded in `native/version.txt`.
- Build-time scripts under `native/scripts/` fetch upstream sources
  by tag at build time (cibuildwheel `before-all` and the sdist build
  hook) so the produced distributions ship the unmodified upstream
  artifacts.
